# Git Conventions

## Commit Messages

Use conventional commits format:

```
type(scope): description

feat(web): add user profile page
fix(server): handle null email in user creation
chore(db): add posts table schema
docs: update API reference for user endpoints
```

### Types

- `feat` — new feature
- `fix` — bug fix
- `chore` — maintenance (deps, config, tooling)
- `docs` — documentation only
- `refactor` — code restructuring with no behavior change
- `test` — adding or updating tests
- `style` — formatting, whitespace changes

### Scopes

Use the app or package name: `web`, `admin`, `server`, `react-native`, `remotion`, `docs`, `db`

Omit scope for cross-cutting changes (e.g., `chore: update turbo.json`).

## Branching

- `main` — production-ready code
- `feat/[description]` — feature branches
- `fix/[description]` — bug fix branches

## What to Commit

- Always run `pnpm lint` and `pnpm check-types` before committing
- Never commit `.env` files (only `.env.example`)
- Commit `pnpm-lock.yaml` changes
- Do not commit `node_modules`, `.next`, `dist`, or build artifacts
